  "firstAcquaintance": "One of the guild's maids, currently practicing for marriage. Just an internship, not actually getting married yet.",
  "personality": "Naive and kind-hearted, optimistic, able to befriend anyone.",
  "like": "Femur bones, wedding dresses",
  "familiarData": "Amel puts on a pure white wedding dress and walks into the chapel -- of course, a certain honorary demon would never let Amel actually get married. Wearing the wedding dress is just for work.\nBecoming a bride is Amel's dream, but there are many things she must learn before that, such as shooting all suitors away--!\n(Mysterious voice: Master, stop feeding her strange knowledge.)\n\nThere is quite a lot to learn about marriage. Fortunately, there is an experienced wife in the guild who can teach hands-on, instructing Amel how to handle men and eliminate scoundrels.\n(Mysterious voice: Hey, don't teach her weird things either.)\n\nAmel's dream is to become a gentle and graceful woman like the Ghost tribe mother, as good at caring for others as her own mother. However, that is something accumulated over time and cannot be rushed, so this graduation certificate is quite difficult to obtain... and a certain honorary demon would never issue it either.",
